This document outlines what constitutes acceptable use of contents and services of the Wallcraft mobile application, available in the Google Play store at the link. 

Please read these Terms carefully before using the Wallcraft mobile application (\"Mobile application\", \"application\" or \"App\") developed by Eastwood company (the \"Developer\"). Downloading and using this App you confirm the accepting and compliance with these Terms. The Terms apply to all users, who downloaded and installed Wallcraft app. By using this application and downloading files, you acknowledge that you have read and agreed with the Terms. If you disagree with any of the terms, you must stop using the App, uninstall the App on your device and remove the content, uploaded from the Wallcraft application. 

This agreement may be revised or updated without notice. 

Overview 

Wallcraft application allows you a free download of the images and to use them only as a desktop Wallpaper. 

All of the content in the App received from open sources on the internet and it\'s protected by the copyright. The copyright of the images belong to their respective owners. 

The user agrees that all contents and services in the App may be accompanied by advertising. The user agrees that application Developer does not bear any responsibility and does not have any obligations in relation with such advertising. 

Copyright

All images posted in the App, received from the wallpaperscraft.com web site.

Although published content is believed to be authorized for sharing and personal use as a desktop wallpaper, unless otherwise noted in the wallpaper description. All images in this App are copyrighted by their respective authors. If you want to use these images in any other way you must get permission from their respective authors. Application Developer is not responsible for the misuse of content posted in the App. 

Developer do not take any responsibility for any damage caused through usage of these files.
If you are the author and you want unauthorized content to be removed from Wallcraft application, please read the Copyright and contact us. 

The user confirms that he is familiar with all clauses of this terms and accepts them unconditionally.
